e=Water Temperature Table of All Coastal Regions|accessdate=August 5, 2019}}</ref>}}\n\n==Ecology==\n\nAccording to the [[A. W. Kuchler]] U.S. [[potential natural vegetation]] types, Seaside Heights, New Jersey would have a dominant vegetation type of Northern [[Cordgrass]] (''73'') with a dominant vegetation form of [[Coastal]] [[Prairie]] (''20'').<ref name=\"Conservation Biology Institute\">{{cite web|url=https://databasin.org/datasets/1c7a301c8e6843f2b4fe63fdb3a9fe39|accessdate=August 5, 2019|title=U.S. Potential Natural Vegetation, Original Kuchler Types, v2.0 (Spatially Adjusted to Correct Geometric Distortions)}}</ref>\n\n==Popular culture==\n[[File:Jack & Bill's Bar.jpeg|thumb|right|Jack & Bill's Bar, a landmark watering hole in Seaside Heights.]]\nSeaside Heights was the setting for MTV's reality TV series ''[[Jersey Shore (TV series)|Jersey Shore]]''.  The first season of ''Jersey Shore'' was filmed in Seaside Heights and [[Toms River, New Jersey|Toms River]] during August 2009. The show's third season was also filmed in Seaside Heights, during July, August, and September 2010.<ref name=ppc>Reiss, Fraidy. [http://www.app.com/article/20091129/NEWS/91129051/Residents+express+anger+with+MTV+ \"Shore residents express anger with MTV's ''Jersey Shore'' premise\"], ''[[Asbury Park Press]]'', November 30, 2009. Accessed January 25, 2015.</ref> After [[New York City]] officials nixed MTV's plans to hold a \"[[Snooki]] Drop\" at its studios in [[Times Square]] alongside the square's [[Times Square Ball|own ball drop]], the event was moved to Seaside Heights.<ref>Schwartz, Alison. [http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20453878,00.html \"Snooki's New Year's Eve Ball to Drop in New Jersey\"], ''[[People (magazine)]]'', December 31, 2010. Accessed July 13, 2011. \"Nicole 'Snooki' Polizzi will drop inside a ball on New Year's Eve in a location where she has fallen before: The Jersey Shore. Although it was reported earlier this month that the MTV reality star would ring in 2011 in New York City's Times Square, the location has been switched to Seaside Heights, N.J., where season 1 and the upcoming season 3 of ''Jersey Shore'' were filmed.\"</ref>  The show returned to Seaside Heights for its fifth season, which wrapped filming on August 2, 2011 and began airing in January 2012.<ref>[http://www.realityaired.com/2011/shows/the-jersey-shore/jersey-shore-season-5-wraps-up-filming/ \"'Jersey Shore' Season 5 Wraps Up Filming\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111019090731/http://www.realityaired.com/2011/shows/the-jersey-shore/jersey-shore-season-5-wraps-up-filming/ |date=October 19, 2011 }}, RealityAired.com.</ref>\n\nPrior to ''Jersey Shore'', the town was also the setting of [[MTV]]'s ''True Life: I Have A Summer Share'', which was filmed in Seaside Heights, as was MTV's ''True Life: I'm a Jersey Shore Girl'' from 2004, which was one of the network's first stories of [[guidette]]s looking for the perfect [[Guido (slang)|guido]].<ref name=Sentinel>Jones, Marilyn. [http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/2010-07-11/travel/os-being-there-nj-071110-20100711_1_shore-thing-mtv-fame-boardwalk \"Being there: New Jersey -- Seaside Heights popular, even without MTV fame\"], ''[[Orlando Sentinel]]'', July 11, 2010. Accessed July 13, 2011. \"MTV has been rocking the shore town since 1998, and again in 2002, when Seaside Heights was selected as the site for Total Request Live and other shows including Shore Thing. MTV also filmed True Life: I Have A Summer Share in Seaside Heights, and rock bands including Bon Jovi have used the borough visually for album covers and music videos.\"</ref><ref>Nark, Jason. [http://articles.philly.com/2010-07-31/news/24969144_1_j-woww-nicole-snooki-polizzi-mtv-beach-house \"Seaside Heights cashing in on 'Jersey Shore'\"], ''[[The Philadelphia Inquirer]]'', July 31, 2010. Accessed July 13, 2011. \"In 2004, MTV's ''True Life: I'm a Jersey Shore Girl'' first chronicled the spectacle of spray-tanned, tough-talking 'guidettes' who invaded Ocean and Monmouth counties' Shore towns each summer to bag a buff 'guido' with gleaming spikes atop his head.\"</ref> Additionally, the MTV summer beach house was located in Seaside Heights for many summers in the early 2000s.<ref name=Sentinel/><ref>Pritchard, Michael. [http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=AC&p_theme=ac&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0F30415D36217494&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM \"MTV'S 'SHORE THING' BACK IN SEASIDE HEIGHTS\"], ''[[The Press of Atlantic City]]'', April 19, 2002. Accessed July 13, 2011. \"Being cool in Seaside Heights will be a \"Shore Thing\" this summer as MTV announced it is returning to the resort for its annual summer beach house location. The network will take over a beach house adjacent to the resort's boardwalk for ''MTV's Shore Thing,'' the name of the network's summer programming.\"</ref>\n\nIn 1985, New Jersey rock band [[Bon Jovi]] filmed most of their music video for the song \"[[In and Out of Love (Bon Jovi song)|In and Out of Love]]\" in Seaside Heights, mainly on the boardwalk.<ref name=Sentinel/><ref>[http://nj-guido.com/wow-bon-jovi-music-video-filmed-entirely-in-seaside-heigts/ Wow! \u2013 Bon Jovi Music Video Filmed Entirely In Seaside Heights, New Jersey \u2013 Back In 1985]</ref>\n\nPortions of the [[2006 in film|2006]] movie ''[[Artie Lange's Beer League]]'' were filmed in Seaside Heights.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0453453/locations Filming locations for Beer League], [[Internet Movie Database]]. Accessed August 6, 2007.</ref>\n\nThe ABC soap opera ''[[One Life to Live]]'' filmed a portion of its 2008 storyline in Seaside Heights, mainly on the beach and boardwalk.<ref>Staff. [https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/app/access/1713024501.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Mar+30%2C+2008&author=CHELSEA+MICHELS&pub=Asbury+Park+Press&desc=Soap+opera+%22One+Life+To+Live%22+to+be+filmed+on+boardwalk&pqatl=google \"Soap opera \"One Life To Live\" to be filmed on boardwalk\"], ''[[Asbury Park Press]]'', March 30, 2008. Accessed July 13, 2011. \"Filming for the soap opera ''One Life To Live'' is scheduled for the week of April 14 at popular Seaside Heights boardwalk spots including Casino Pier...\"</ref>\n\nThe song 'Mera Dil Tera Deewana' from the 1999 Hindi film [[Aa Ab Laut Chalen]] directed by [[Rishi Kapoor]] and starring [[Akshaye Khanna]] and [[Aishwarya Rai]] was shot at Seaside Heights.\n\n==Notable people==\n{{Category see also|People from Seaside Heights, New Jersey}}\nPeople who were born in, residents of, or otherwise closely associated with Seaside Heights include:\n* [[Fred Ashton (politician)|Fred Ashton]] (1931-2013), politician who served as the Mayor of [[Easton, Pennsylvania]] from 1968 to 1976.<ref>Staff. [http://www.lehighvalleylive.com/easton/index.ssf/2013/05/former_easton_mayor_fred_ashto.html \"Former Easton Mayor Fred Ashton dies\"], ''[[Express-Times]]'', May 9, 2013. Accessed August 10, 2014. \"Ashton lived in Seaside Heights, N.J., but died in the home of his sister, Anna, where he had been staying since Superstorm Sandy struck.\"</ref>\n* [[Lou Taylor Pucci]] (born 1985), actor.<ref>O'Sullivan, Eleanor. [https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/app/access/1772293801.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Jan+22%2C+2006&author=ELEANOR+O'SULLIVAN&pub=Asbury+Park+Press&desc=COMING+TUESDAY+ON+DVD&pqatl=google \"Coming Tuesday on DVD\"], ''[[Asbury Park Press]]'', January 22, 2006. Accessed June 10, 2013. \"Lou Taylor Pucci of Seaside Heights stars in ''Thumbsucker,'' a dark comedy arriving on the home viewing market this week.\"</ref>\n* [[Robbie E]] (born 1983), professional wrestler.<ref>Bishop, Matt. [http://slam.canoe.com/Slam/Wrestling/2010/12/03/16411486.html \"Impact: Anderson, Angle return as TNA heads to Final Resolution\"], Slam Sports, December 3, 2010. Accessed July 22, 2015. \"Introducing first, repping Seaside Heights, NJ is Robbie E.\"</ref>\n* [[Immanuel Velikovsky]] (1895-1979), author known for his controversial books reinterpreting the events of ancient history, in particular the bestseller ''[[Worlds in Collision]]''.<ref>[http://abob.libs.uga.edu/bobk/vwhelton.html \"Whelton_in Unordnung\"]. Accessed July 22, 2015. \"He possesses a very tenacious memory that I am reminded of every time he tells his version of the problems with Sagan's infamous probability calculation exactly as I explained it to him on the drive back from Velikovsky's house at Seaside Heights, New Jersey, in July 1978.\"</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n{{wikivoyage|Seaside Heights}}\n{{Portal|New Jersey|Biography|Politics}}\n* [http://www.seaside-heightsnj.org/ Seaside Heights website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20051201144648/http://www.ssheights.k12.nj.us/ Seaside Heights Public School]\n* {{NJReportCard|29|4710|050|Hugh J. Boyd Jr. Elementary School}}\n* [https://nces.ed.gov/ccd/schoolsearch/school_list.asp?Search=1&DistrictID=3414790 School Data for the Seaside Heights Public School], [[National Center for Education Statistics]]\n* [https://www.centralreg.k12.nj.us/ Central Regional School District]\n* [http://www.shfd44.com/news/index/layoutfile/home Seaside Heights Volunteer Fire Department Station 44]\n* [http://tri-borofirstaid.com/ Tri-Boro First Aid Squad 40]\n* [http://www.discoverseasideheights.com/ Discover Seaside Heights]\n* [http://www.seasideheightsnjonline.com/ Seaside Heights NJ Online]\n* [http://www.seasideheights.org/ Seaside Heights Memorabilia Website]\n* [http://www.visitnjshore.com/seaside-heights/ Seaside Heights New Jersey Shore Travel Information]\n* [http://www.christophervaz.com/ Seaside Heights History Website]\n* [http://talesofthejerseyshore.blogspot.com/2009/06/freeman-pier-fire-1955-seaside.html The Freeman Pier Fire- 1955- Seaside]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{Succession box\n | title  = Beaches of New Jersey\n | years  = \